<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="722" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">840.51 Frozen Credits/4362: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-13T14:00:00+09:00">November 13,
                                1941—2 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received November 22—1:36 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1795. On November 11, 1941, the Japanese Government published in the <hi rend="italic">Official Gazette</hi> general licenses Nos. 61 and 62 of
                        the Ministry of Finance which in effect unfreeze American Government
                        establishments and personnel in Japan.</p>
                    <p>[Here follow texts of translations of the general licenses.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>